Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the noodles.

Strip the leafy part of the @kale{80%grams} from the stem. Chop the leaves into
bite-sized pieces. Discard the stems (they're too tough to eat).

Spread the kale out on a lined #baking tray{}.

Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. When
the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until crispy, ~{6-8%mins}.

> TIP: Watch the kale closely so it doesn't burn.

When the water is boiling, add the @egg noodles{150%grams} and cook until softened,
~{4-6%mins}.

Drain in a #sieve{} then return to the pot, off the heat. Drizzle with oil and toss
to prevent sticking.

While the noodles cook, halve the @baby corn{150%grams} lengthways.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @shallot{1}.

Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways
into small pieces.

== Stir-Fry ==

Place a large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, fry the carrot, shallot and corn until tender, stirring often,
~{6-8%mins}.

Add @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} and @garlic, ginger & lemongrass paste{1%sachet}.
Cook until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Add @teriyaki sauce{2%sachets} and @water{150%ml} (double for 4p). Stir until
warmed through.

Remove from the heat and mix in the @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet}. Season to taste
with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if necessary.

Stir the drained noodles through the sauce until well coated and warmed through.

Divide your fragrant veggie noodles between bowls.

Top with the crispy roasted kale.